<h4>Design</h4><div class="skills-group left-container"><div class="skill xd"><figure><span>XD</span></figure><div class="description right"><h4>XD</h4><p>This is where I spend the most of my time when I work on design. Prototypes, interaction and final design are made here.</p></div></div><div class="skill ai"><figure><span>Ai</span></figure><div class="description right"><h4>Illustrator</h4><p>I use it mostly to get graphics on SVG format for web platform, usually branding or icons.</p></div></div><div class="skill ps"><figure><span>PS</span></figure><div class="description right"><h4>Photoshp</h4><p>I use photoshop to make small retouches that a website/application image may need.</p></div></div></div><h4>Development</h4><div class="skills-group left-container"><div class="skill an"><figure class="loading"><div class="loader"><div></div><div></div></div><img data-src="img/skills/angular.svg" alt=""></figure><div class="description right"><h4>Angular JS</h4><p>I've worked 5 years with it using the v1.5. While this framework is almost deprecated, it was a good experience to use almost every aspect of it.</p></div></div><div class="skill bs"><figure class="loading"><div class="loader"><div></div><div></div></div><img data-src="img/skills/bootstrap.svg" alt=""></figure><div class="description right"><h4>Bootstrap</h4><p>I'm comfortable using it's layout, components and events.</p></div></div><div class="skill jq"><figure class="loading"><div class="loader"><div></div><div></div></div><img data-src="img/skills/jquery.svg" alt=""></figure><div class="description right"><h4>jQuery</h4><p>Altough we could consider jQuery as deprecared for new projects, there are still many websites using it. I had my jQuery days, so I can work with legacy code using it.</p></div></div><div class="skill js"><figure class="loading"><div class="loader"><div></div><div></div></div><img data-src="img/skills/js.svg" alt=""></figure><div class="description right"><h4>JS Next</h4><p>Javascript is the base of my work as frontend developer, I keep myself updated about the newer versions features.</p></div></div><div class="skill css"><figure class="loading"><div class="loader"><div></div><div></div></div><img data-src="img/skills/css.svg" alt=""></figure><div class="description right"><h4>CSS3</h4><p>8 years using CSS, 5 years using LESS and SASS preprocessors. I'm fully comfortable working with any of them.</p></div></div><div class="skill html"><figure class="loading"><div class="loader"><div></div><div></div></div><img data-src="img/skills/html.svg" alt=""></figure><div class="description right"><h4>HTML 5</h4><p>Over the years, I've got the chance to work with every aspect of HTML and it's API's.</p></div></div><div class="skill wordpress"><figure class="loading"><div class="loader"><div></div><div></div></div><img data-src="img/skills/wordpress.svg" alt=""></figure><div class="description right"><h4>Wordpress</h4><p>With 5+ of experience with the CMS, I feel very comfortable working with it. I had the chance to do few plugins and themes on it.</p></div></div><div class="skill mysql"><figure class="loading"><div class="loader"><div></div><div></div></div><img data-src="img/skills/mysql.svg" alt=""></figure><div class="description right"><h4>MySQL</h4><p>Definitely not my area, but I do undersand how querys are built, worked with it few years ago.</p></div></div><div class="skill php"><figure class="loading"><div class="loader"><div></div><div></div></div><img data-src="img/skills/php.svg" alt=""></figure><div class="description right"><h4>PHP</h4><p>Most of my experience on it was aim to wordpress project and a couple of MVC systems. I'm not an expert, but I do get my way around it.</p></div></div><div class="skill react"><figure class="loading"><div class="loader"><div></div><div></div></div><img data-src="img/skills/react-native.svg" alt=""></figure><div class="description right"><h4>React Native</h4><p>Currently learning and developing a small pet project.</p></div></div><div class="skill react"><figure class="loading"><div class="loader"><div></div><div></div></div><img data-src="img/skills/react.svg" alt=""></figure><div class="description right"><h4>React</h4><p>Did one project a couple of years ago (not online anymore). I am familiar the JSX philosophy and the use of hooks for state management.</p></div></div><div class="skill vue"><figure class="loading"><div class="loader"><div></div><div></div></div><img data-src="img/skills/vue.svg" alt=""></figure><div class="description right"><h4>Vue JS</h4><p>Used in a wordpress plugin project. It was a reduced version of a SAAS product for our customers.</p></div></div></div></div><div><h4>Tooling</h4><div class="skills-group"><div class="skill git"><figure class="loading"><div class="loader"><div></div><div></div></div><img data-src="img/skills/git.svg" alt=""></figure><div class="description left"><h4>Git</h4><p>I use git from command line following, documented guidelines. Over the years, I have combined git with github, gitlab, bitbucket and helix.</p></div></div><div class="skill node"><figure class="loading"><div class="loader"><div></div><div></div></div><img data-src="img/skills/node.svg" alt=""></figure><div class="description left"><h4>Node</h4><p>Mostly used as complement for task runners, I do not have experience working with node as backend language.</p></div></div><div class="skill grunt"><figure class="loading"><div class="loader"><div></div><div></div></div><img data-src="img/skills/grunt.svg" alt=""></figure><div class="description left"><h4>Grunt</h4><p>Used for CSS preprocessors, JS transpilation, file concatenation, image minification, theming, productivity engagment and more.</p></div></div><div class="skill webpack"><figure class="loading"><div class="loader"><div></div><div></div></div><img data-src="img/skills/webpack.svg" alt=""></figure><div class="description left"><h4>Webpack</h4><p>Used for CSS preprocessors, JS transpilation, file concatenation, image minification, theming, productivity engagment and more.</p></div></div><div class="skill gulp"><figure class="loading"><div class="loader"><div></div><div></div></div><img data-src="img/skills/gulp.svg" alt=""></figure><div class="description left"><h4>Gulp</h4><p>Used for CSS preprocessors, JS transpilation, file concatenation, image minification, theming, productivity engagment and more.</p></div></div><div class="skill trello"><figure class="loading"><div class="loader"><div></div><div></div></div><img data-src="img/skills/trello.svg" alt=""></figure><div class="description left"><h4>Trello</h4><p>Used to manage tasks and set sprints for the next version of the software.</p></div></div></div><h4>Server</h4><div class="skills-group"><div class="skill aws"><figure class="loading"><div class="loader"><div></div><div></div></div><img data-src="img/skills/aws.svg" alt=""></figure><div class="description left"><h4>AWS EC2</h4><p>I have set an instance running ubuntu sever for a small sized ecommerce.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></section><section id="experience" data-index="3"><nav id="projects-nav"><button class="btn-main" data-direction="prev"><svg aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" data-prefix="fas" data-icon="arrow-up" class="svg-inline--fa fa-arrow-up fa-w-14" role="img" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 448 512"><path fill="#FFF" d="M34.9 289.5l-22.2-22.2c-9.4-9.4-9.4-24.6 0-33.9L207 39c9.4-9.4 24.6-9.4 33.9 0l194.3 194.3c9.4 9.4 9.4 24.6 0 33.9L413 289.4c-9.5 9.5-25 9.3-34.3-.4L264 168.6V456c0 13.3-10.7 24-24 24h-32c-13.3 0-24-10.7-24-24V168.6L69.2 289.1c-9.3 9.8-24.8 10-34.3.4z"></path></svg></button> <span>1 / 8</span> <button class="btn-main" data-direction="next"><svg aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" data-prefix="fas" data-icon="arrow-down" class="svg-inline--fa fa-arrow-down fa-w-14" role="img" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 448 512"><path fill="#FFF" d="M413.1 222.5l22.2 22.2c9.4 9.4 9.4 24.6 0 33.9L241 473c-9.4 9.4-24.6 9.4-33.9 0L12.7 278.6c-9.4-9.4-9.4-24.6 0-33.9l22.2-22.2c9.5-9.5 25-9.3 34.3.4L184 343.4V56c0-13.3 10.7-24 24-24h32c13.3 0 24 10.7 24 24v287.4l114.8-120.5c9.3-9.8 24.8-10 34.3-.4z"></path></svg></button></nav><div id="projects-container"><div class="project"><div class="blurred-container"><article><div class="meta-container"><figure class="loading"><div class="loader"><div></div><div></div></div><img data-src="img/projects/stim-cover.jpg" alt="stim-social"></figure><div class="file"><div><span>Since</span><p>Late 2015</p></div><div><span>Status</span><p>Maintenance</p></div><div><span>Company</span><p>Stim Social</p></div><div><span>Based</span><p>Salt lake City, Utah</p></div></div><div class="buttons-container double"><button class="btn-main demo-btn" data-target="stim-demo">Demo</button> <a class="btn-main" href="https://stimsocial.com/" rel="nofollow" target="blank"><svg aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" data-prefix="fas" data-icon="external-link-alt" class="svg-inline--fa fa-external-link-alt fa-w-16" role="img" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 512 512"><path fill="#FFF" d="M432,320H400a16,16,0,0,0-16,16V448H64V128H208a16,16,0,0,0,16-16V80a16,16,0,0,0-16-16H48A48,48,0,0,0,0,112V464a48,48,0,0,0,48,48H400a48,48,0,0,0,48-48V336A16,16,0,0,0,432,320ZM488,0h-128c-21.37,0-32.05,25.91-17,41l35.73,35.73L135,320.37a24,24,0,0,0,0,34L157.67,377a24,24,0,0,0,34,0L435.28,133.32,471,169c15,15,41,4.5,41-17V24A24,24,0,0,0,488,0Z"></path></svg> Website</a></div></div><div class="info"><div class="title"><h5>Project</h5><h2>Stim <span>Social</span></h2></div><div class="content"><p>This is my biggest project, working on it for the last 5 years. It is a SAAS product for a company based on Salt Lake City, Utah.</p><p>My main role on this project is solo frontend developer. Most of the software communicates with the backend through a REST API over JSON.</p><p>My work here consisted on making the UI of a dashboard with +26 unique views, for customers to create their Stim accounts, add their social media accounts (instagram & tiktok) and manage them through a series of targets, settings and several reports.</p><p>The design was already done when I joined, so I only had to create new components when needed, using the visual scheme that was already done.</p><p>This web app is based on a Opencart installation, with Paypal, Braintree and Stripe integrations for payments.</p><p>After 2 years of working on this project, I was required to find a way to create a cloned version of the app so new partners could have their own branded version of it.<br>This was made using Grunt and Node; running a node command, the default theme would be cloned into a directory using the new brand name, with customization capability and getting new features and changes from the default theme as they were are added.</p><p>This project is on maintenance since August, 2020.</p><br></div></div></article></div></div><div class="project"><div class="blurred-container"><article><div class="meta-container"><figure class="loading"><div class="loader"><div></div><div></div></div><img data-src="img/projects/agency-cover.jpg" alt="Agency Dashboard Cover"></figure><div class="file"><div><span>Since</span><p>2018</p></div><div><span>Status</span><p>Maintenance</p></div><div><span>Company</span><p>Stim Social</p></div><div><span>Based</span><p>Salt lake City, Utah</p></div></div><div class="buttons-container"><button class="btn-main demo-btn" data-target="agency-demo">Demo</button></div></div><div class="info"><div class="title"><h5>Project</h5><h2>Agency <span>Dashboard</span></h2></div><div class="content"><p>Another project of the Stim Social family. This is a Wordpress plugin, for marketing/advertising agencies to install in their website and get a reduced version of Stim's dashboard.</p><p>I was the only developer working on the plugin creation.<br>The frontend is made with Vue, LESS and Grunt, the backend uses the Stim API to send and recieve data, and authorization is made with tokens.</p></div><footer></footer></div></article></div></div><div class="project"><div class="blurred-container"><article><div class="meta-container"><figure class="cover loading"><div class="loader"><div></div><div></div></div><img data-src="img/projects/lana-cover.jpg" alt="stim-social"></figure><div class="file"><div><span>Since</span><p>2020</p></div><div><span>Status</span><p>Maintenance</p></div><div><span>Company</span><p>Lana</p></div><div><span>Based</span><p>Córdoba, Argentina</p></div></div><div class="buttons-container"><a class="btn-main" href="https://lanaindumentaria.com.ar/" target="blank"><svg aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" data-prefix="fas" data-icon="external-link-alt" class="svg-inline--fa fa-external-link-alt fa-w-16" role="img" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 512 512"><path fill="#FFF" d="M432,320H400a16,16,0,0,0-16,16V448H64V128H208a16,16,0,0,0,16-16V80a16,16,0,0,0-16-16H48A48,48,0,0,0,0,112V464a48,48,0,0,0,48,48H400a48,48,0,0,0,48-48V336A16,16,0,0,0,432,320ZM488,0h-128c-21.37,0-32.05,25.91-17,41l35.73,35.73L135,320.37a24,24,0,0,0,0,34L157.67,377a24,24,0,0,0,34,0L435.28,133.32,471,169c15,15,41,4.5,41-17V24A24,24,0,0,0,488,0Z"></path></svg> Website</a></div></div><div class="info"><div class="title"><h5>Project</h5><h2>Lana <span>Indumentaria</span></h2></div><div class="content"><p>I co-own this website with my sister. This is a fashion ecommerce platform built in wordpress.</p><p>I use a base repo created by me, which brings a grunt configuration with a css preprocesor (LESS with autoprefixer), JS+ to JS 5 transpiling, image compresion (tinyimg) and minification (CSS & JS) integrated.<br>This repository also comes with a speed optimized theme <a href="#">(astra)</a> as a base and it get's improved and customized by myself, integrating several marketing tools and keeping a region-optimized speed.</p><p>For this project, I've setted up an AWS EC2 instance, running ubuntu server 2016 with apache, php and mysql. Emails are set up using a combination of gmail with an external service (ImprovMX).</p><p>Payments are made with woocommerce and a local payment gateway. It allows credit cards, bank wires and "cash" (by printing a payment ticket).</p><p>It is integrated with Facebook shop, facebook pixel, google ads and mailchimp.</p></div></div></article></div></div><div class="project"><div class="blurred-container"><article><div class="meta-container"><figure class="cover loading"><div class="loader"><div></div><div></div></div><img data-src="img/projects/camote-cover.jpg" alt="Camote cover"></figure><div class="file"><div><span>Year</span><p>2017</p></div><div><span>Status</span><p>Ended</p></div><div><span>Company</span><p>Camote</p></div><div><span>Based</span><p>Córdoba, Argentina</p></div></div></div><div class="info"><div class="title"><h5>Project</h5><h2>Camote</h2></div><div class="content"><p>This was an ecommerce website for a store in the health products business.</p><p>The frontend consisted of a customized React app, with Redux, Webpack and SASS.</p><p>This business is not open anymore, so the website is not online.</p></div></div></article></div></div><div class="project"><div class="blurred-container"><article><div class="meta-container"><figure class="loading"><div class="loader"><div></div><div></div></div><img data-src="img/projects/seres-cover.jpg" alt="Seres Cover"></figure><div class="file"><div><span>Year</span><p>2016</p></div><div><span>Status</span><p>Maintenance</p></div><div><span>Company</span><p>Seres</p></div><div><span>Based</span><p>Córdoba, Argentina</p></div></div><div class="buttons-container"><a class="btn-main" href="https://www.serespaliativa.com.ar/" target="blank"><svg aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" data-prefix="fas" data-icon="external-link-alt" class="svg-inline--fa fa-external-link-alt fa-w-16" role="img" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 512 512"><path fill="#FFF" d="M432,320H400a16,1